      "content": "It's not just part of getting older, it's a sign that your asthma is flaring up. You should definitely be worried. I recommend you take a couple of puffs from your inhaler, and if that doesn't help, try taking a few extra puffs every 15 minutes for the next hour. If you still feel short of breath, you might want to consider taking a dose of your asthma medication, but only if you have it. And if you don't, you should definitely get it from a pharmacy. Just remember, it's better to be safe than sorry, so don't wait too long.",
